NACL
✅ Full Form

NACL = Network Access Control List

✅ What is NACL?

NACL is a firewall applied at subnet level.

It controls:

Allowed traffic
Denied traffic

for entire subnet.

🧠 How NACL Works
Internet
   ↓
NACL (Subnet Firewall)
   ↓
EC2 Instances
✅ Example Rules
ALLOW  HTTP   80
ALLOW  HTTPS  443
DENY   ALL OTHER TRAFFIC
⚡ Stateless Nature

NACL is stateless.

Meaning:

If inbound allowed → outbound must also be allowed separately.

🔥 Security Group vs NACL
Feature	Security Group	NACL
Applied To	EC2 Instance	Subnet
Stateful	✅ Yes	❌ No
Default Behavior	Allow	Deny
Used By Developers	Very Often	Rarely Modified
